post_text: The annual student art contest from the City of Englewood, CO - Government is open! We can't wait to see your submissions.
shared_text:
City of Englewood, CO - Government
August 31 at 7:34 AM ·

Calling All Student Artists 🎨

Each year, the City of Englewood releases a calendar featuring creations by some of the community’s most talented student artists. We’re looking ahead to 2021 and now is the time to submit your artwork for consideration.

The Student Art Contest is open to Englewood students from Kindergarten through 12th Grade. The total number of entries will be narrowed down to 50 and artwork included in the calendar will receive recognition by City Council.

Submissions are due September 18 and must have an entry form attached. We can’t wait to see what you come up with! 😊 Learn more at: http://www.englewoodco.gov/arts-culture/student-art-contest

Englewood Schools

HELP NEEDED: Some Englewood families are in need of food items to get them through the weekends in addition to the free meals we have available Monday through Friday.

Here is the wish list of items: cereal, oatmeal packets, granola bars, microwaveable mac and cheese, boxed tuna/chicken helper style meals, canned tuna, canned chicken, soups with pop tops, Chef Boyardee type of meals, canned veggies, canned fruit or fruit pouches/apple sauce, rice, pasta, pasta sauce-cans, crackers, peanut butter, jelly-plastic bottles.

If you are able to donate, you can bring items to Cafe 180 from 11:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m. or Mosaic Church between 11:00 p.m. and 3:00 p.m. Thanks to Mosaic who will put the weekend bags together for us, and thank you to anyone who is willing to help!

post_text:
Good news! Thanks to the generosity of the Englewood community and Englewood Schools’ PTSAs, all negative lunch balances in the school district have been paid! This means families will not have to worry about carrying over debt from unpaid lunch balances into next year, and that the district will not need to use general fund dollars to pay off lunch debt. Some years the district has paid over $40,000 toward debt from unpaid lunches.

Thank you, Englewood community!
text:
Good news! Thanks to the generosity of the Englewood community and Englewood Schools’ PTSAs, all negative lunch balances in the school district have been paid! This means families will not have to worry about carrying over debt from unpaid lunch balances into next year, and that the district will not need to use general fund dollars to pay off lunch debt. Some years the district has paid over $40,000 toward debt from unpaid lunches.

Thank you, Englewood community!

shared_text:
City of Englewood, CO - Government
April 15 at 9:35 AM ·

Change The Trend has banded together with organizations and churches across Englewood, Littleton, and Sheridan to help those who need it most. They are offering to deliver groceries or provide other critical resources to those who are susceptible to the negative outcomes of COVID-19 (elderly, have lung disease, heart disease, or have a compromised immune system). ❤️

If you or someone you know needs help, please visit https://changethetrend.org/ or call 720-235-8501.

post_text: If you need rent assistance, this program from the City of Englewood, Colorado might help you.
shared_text:
ENGLEWOODCO.GOV
Coronavirus (COVID-19) Resource Center | City of Englewood, Colorado

City of Englewood, CO - Government
April 7 at 9:31 AM ·

Englewood Rent Assistance Program

In light of the hardships some residents may face during this unprecedented time of economic instability, the City of Englewood has created a program to offer financial assistance meant to ease the immediate burden of paying rent.

The Rent Assistance Program is available to Englewood residents with a household income of 175% of the Federal Poverty Level or less.

Learn more and apply at englewoodco.gov/coronavirus under the Community Resources tab. #EnglewoodStrong

March 26 at 10:17 AM ·

GET CONNECTED. GET HELP. Do you have questions about the COVID-19 pandemic? Call 211 and your questions will be answered.

911 dispatchers and the Tri-County Health Department have been overwhelmed with calls so we are asking the community to please use 211 beginning TODAY. This new service, available 8am-5pm Monday-Friday, will help you with all your COVID-19 needs. There is even access to a language translation service to accommodate over 170 languages. Stay safe and let's all look out for each other. #BetterTogether

Interested in careers in agriculture, architecture, business, renewable energy, engineering, construction, or veterinary medicine? The Sustainable Agriculture & Green Energy (SAGE) pathway offered at CFHSC may be a strong fit for you. Through SAGE, students are learning about hydroponics and aquaponics, and the ever-popular farm-to-table operations such as raising backyard chickens, composting, community gardening, and bee-keeping.

The Sustainable Agriculture & Green Energy (SAGE) pathway offered at CFHSC may be a strong fit for you. Through SAGE, students are learning about hydroponics and aquaponics, and the ever-popular farm-to-table operations such as raising backyard chickens, composting, community gardening, and bee-keeping.

post_text:
Offered at Englewood High School and Colorado’s Finest High School of Choice, the Computer Science
Pathway is a strong fit for students who like to learn about technology and are interested in building
knowledge of the latest industry advances and trends.

“The problem solving they’re learning is applicable to all content areas,” Dr. James, EHS Computer Science pathway educator.

The Computer Science Pathway is part of our district’s STEAM education program, which offers students hands-on pathways to gain deeper knowledge in science, technology, engineering, arts, and math subjects. Find out if a STEAM pathway is a good fit for you. www.englewoodschools.net/steam.

post_text:
Next week (March 2 - 6) is National School Breakfast Week and Englewood elementary schools are planning some fun activities to celebrate the benefits of school breakfast! We hope everyone will join us in our celebration by:

-DECORATING: Coloring pages will be sent home in Friday folders this week.Students are encouraged to color them and give them to kitchen staff on Monday to help decorate the cafeteria.

-WINNING PRIZES: Students who eat school breakfast every day of the week (March 2 - 6) will be entered to win a raffle prize! Prizes will be awarded on Friday, March 6.

-PARTICIPATING IN ACTIVITIES: During breakfast, we will be sampling new breakfast items, giving away t-shirts and will have a photo booth!

#NSBW2020 #schoolnutrition

post_text: DEMOLITION UPDATE and PARKING CHANGES at ECE: Demolition of the old Maddox building is currently scheduled for the first week of February. Beginning February 3, the current ECE Maddox parking lot off of S. Huron St. will be closed and a temporary lot will be opened on S. Galapago. A new, large parking lot is scheduled to be complete at the end of March! Until then, we ask families to continue to use street parking around Maddox and only use the Galapago lot if you have a handicapped placard or other permit. Thank you for your patience!

Beginning February 3, the current ECE Maddox parking lot off of S. Huron St. will be closed and a temporary lot will be opened on S. Galapago. A new, large parking lot is scheduled to be complete at the end of March! post_text: In our close-knit community, Englewood Schools' Board Members are people you know: your neighbors, fellow parents and friends. They’re also unpaid volunteers who devote countless hours to making sure our district is the best it can be. January is school board appreciation month, and we hope that you’ll join us in showing appreciation for our five board members who are so dedicated to the success of each student in our district. Next time you see them — at morning drop-off, at the grocery store or around the neighborhood — be sure to thank them for all that they do. #belongandthrive #schoolboardmonth

Today, October 29 all high school and middle school Englewood Schools students, including E.M.S., E.L.A., E.H.S. and Colorado's Finest, will be released at 1:30 p.m. Students who normally ride the bus can get on the bus at that time.

Elementary and FULL DAY preschool students will be released at their normal time. However, parents who are able and would like to may pick up their student earlier. High School and Middle School students are being released earlier so they can be home to take care of younger siblings if needed.

All PART DAY, AFTERNOON ONLY ECE classes are cancelled for today.

After school activities and childcare are cancelled.

post_text:
The Englewood Schools Board of Education is seeking a new member to be appointed through an application and interview process for a two year term beginning on November 19, 2019.

Interested parties may apply through the link below. The application is due by November 11, 2019. The Board will interview selected applicants the evening of November 14, 2019 (by invitation.)

To be eligible for appointment, an applicant must reside in Englewood School District and must have been a registered elector of the Englewood School District for at least twelve consecutive months prior to the date of appointment. The applicant must also be 18 years of age or older, a United States citizen and never been convicted of a sexual offense against a child.
